                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.857 An 2/96½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <gloss type="from">Wilson</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hot Springs, Va.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">26 December, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: This is encouraging as to the
                    spirit of the Austro-Hungarian government, but I fear they are preparing to
                    contest the facts with us, and the inferences to be drawn from them.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
